- End with `*/`

CSS comments can be:
1. Single-line comments
2. Multi-line comments

Both use the same `/* */` syntax.

For the given CSS code:
```css
div {
    margin: 0 auto;
    width: 50%;
    text-align: center;
}
```

To add a comment, I would use the `/* */` syntax. A meaningful comment here could describe what the CSS rule does - in this case, the code is centering a div element on the page (margin: 0 auto centers horizontally, width: 50% gives it a width, and text-align: center centers the text inside).

So I would add a comment like:
```css
/* Center the div element on the page */ 
div {
    margin: 0 auto;
    width: 50%;
    text-align: center;
}
```

This demonstrates how to properly insert a CSS comment before the rule block to describe its purpose.

